node.text: Long before there was @teachertrauma, there was “Paul’s Mom.” It was my way to vent and ended up hitting too close to home for many 😂 Enjoy.

node.text: Trying to bring some laughter on a stressful election night. I present...Paul’s mom at virtual parent teacher conferences. Paul has opted to learn at home this year. Enjoy!

node.title: Paul’s Mom at Virtual Parent-Teacher Conferences

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 15, 2021. May be a meme of 1 person and text that says 'Me when I do a a bar crawl in the town work in: @teachertrauma'.

Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 14, 2021. May be a meme of 1 person and text that says 'My students when I haven't even gotten halfway through explaining the directions: @teachertrauma I GOT QUESTIONS'.

node.text:
I love watching their hands go down one by one as they let me FINISH SPEAKING. 
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Me when my friends don't understand why I need to spend three hours working on rhyming clues for a scavenger hunt that will take my students 20 minutes: @teachertrauma This is my work, okay, it's important!'.

node.text:
THIS IS VERY IMPORTANT. Hours of work for twenty minutes of solid engagement 😂
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 12, 2021. May be a meme of text that says 'Teachers when the Sunday Scaries start setting in after a glorious stress free summer: @teachertrauma NOT YOU AGAIN.'.

node.text:
I’m just trying to enjoy my life and then Sunday shows up like 👁👄👁
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 10, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'TEACHER TRAUMA Teacher Trauma @TeacherTrauma1 Being a teacher is fun because when you have a pimple, your students walk up to you and point directly at it as if you're not a HUMAN BEING WITH FEELINGS. 4:58 PM 9/10/21 Twitter for iPhone'.

node.text:
Since you mentioned it, it’s just my adult acne, THANKS FOR NOTICING. 😫
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 09, 2021. May be a meme of 2 people and text that says 'My students when they show up late to my class: @teachertrauma IAM so LOST HERE. CAN SOMEONE PLEASE FILL ME IN? UNLESS IT'S BORING AND THEN DON'T.'.

Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Me when someone makes a snide comment about "summers off" without taking into consideration the massive amount of work I do on nights/weekends & low salary: @teachertrauma Look at ty fucking ifo.'.

node.text:
“You don’t know what I deal with every night.” Real Housewives of Beverly Hills…anyone? Anyone? 💎
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Teacher Trauma on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Me when first found out that most teachers don't have to submit weekly formal lesson plans @teachertrauma'.

node.text:
This information hit me like a ton of bricks 😂 Here I am submitting formal plans every week for the past 9 years and some of you have never had to write one. 
.
.
.
.
#teach #teacher #teachers #teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #teachermemes #teacherproblems #teacherhumor #teacherlife
